1. # Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI
2. 
3. Provides an implementation of the `IChatClient` interface for the `OpenAI` package and OpenAI-compatible endpoints.
4. 
5. ## Install the package
6. 
7. From the command-line:
8. 
9. ```console
10. dotnet add package Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI
11. ```
12. 
13. Or directly in the C# project file:
14. 
15. ```xml
16. <ItemGroup>
17.   <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI" Version="[CURRENTVERSION]" />
18. </ItemGroup>
19. ```
20. 
21. ## Usage Examples
22. 
23. ### Chat
24. 
25. ```csharp
26. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
27. 
28. IChatClient client =
29.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
30.     .AsIChatClient();
31. 
32. Console.WriteLine(await client.GetResponseAsync("What is AI?"));
33. ```
34. 
35. ### Chat + Conversation History
36. 
37. ```csharp
38. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
39. 
40. IChatClient client =
41.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
42.     .AsIChatClient();
43. 
44. Console.WriteLine(await client.GetResponseAsync(
45. [
46.     new ChatMessage(ChatRole.System, "You are a helpful AI assistant"),
47.     new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, "What is AI?"),
48. ]));
49. ```
50. 
51. ### Chat streaming
52. 
53. ```csharp
54. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
55. 
56. IChatClient client =
57.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
58.     .AsIChatClient();
59. 
60. await foreach (var update in client.GetStreamingResponseAsync("What is AI?"))
61. {
62.     Console.Write(update);
63. }
64. ```
65. 
66. ### Tool calling
67. 
68. ```csharp
69. using System.ComponentModel;
70. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
71. 
72. IChatClient openaiClient =
73.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
74.     .AsIChatClient();
75. 
76. IChatClient client = new ChatClientBuilder(openaiClient)
77.     .UseFunctionInvocation()
78.     .Build();
79. 
80. ChatOptions chatOptions = new()
81. {
82.     Tools = [AIFunctionFactory.Create(GetWeather)]
83. };
84. 
85. await foreach (var message in client.GetStreamingResponseAsync("Do I need an umbrella?", chatOptions))
86. {
87.     Console.Write(message);
88. }
89. 
90. [Description("Gets the weather")]
91. static string GetWeather() => Random.Shared.NextDouble() > 0.5 ? "It's sunny" : "It's raining";
92. ```
93. 
94. ### Caching
95. 
96. ```csharp
97. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
98. using Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.Distributed;
99. using Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.Memory;
100. using Microsoft.Extensions.Options;
101. 
102. IDistributedCache cache = new MemoryDistributedCache(Options.Create(new MemoryDistributedCacheOptions()));
103. 
104. IChatClient openaiClient =
105.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
106.     .AsIChatClient();
107. 
108. IChatClient client = new ChatClientBuilder(openaiClient)
109.     .UseDistributedCache(cache)
110.     .Build();
111. 
112. for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
113. {
114.     await foreach (var message in client.GetStreamingResponseAsync("In less than 100 words, what is AI?"))
115.     {
116.         Console.Write(message);
117.     }
118. 
119.     Console.WriteLine();
120.     Console.WriteLine();
121. }
122. ```
123. 
124. ### Telemetry
125. 
126. ```csharp
127. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
128. using OpenTelemetry.Trace;
129. 
130. // Configure OpenTelemetry exporter
131. var sourceName = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
132. var tracerProvider = OpenTelemetry.Sdk.CreateTracerProviderBuilder()
133.     .AddSource(sourceName)
134.     .AddConsoleExporter()
135.     .Build();
136. 
137. IChatClient openaiClient =
138.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
139.     .AsIChatClient();
140. 
141. IChatClient client = new ChatClientBuilder(openaiClient)
142.     .UseOpenTelemetry(sourceName: sourceName, configure: c => c.EnableSensitiveData = true)
143.     .Build();
144. 
145. Console.WriteLine(await client.GetResponseAsync("What is AI?"));
146. ```
147. 
148. ### Telemetry, Caching, and Tool Calling
149. 
150. ```csharp
151. using System.ComponentModel;
152. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
153. using Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.Distributed;
154. using Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.Memory;
155. using Microsoft.Extensions.Options;
156. using OpenTelemetry.Trace;
157. 
158. // Configure telemetry
159. var sourceName = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
160. var tracerProvider = OpenTelemetry.Sdk.CreateTracerProviderBuilder()
161.     .AddSource(sourceName)
162.     .AddConsoleExporter()
163.     .Build();
164. 
165. // Configure caching
166. IDistributedCache cache = new MemoryDistributedCache(Options.Create(new MemoryDistributedCacheOptions()));
167. 
168. // Configure tool calling
169. var chatOptions = new ChatOptions
170. {
171.     Tools = [AIFunctionFactory.Create(GetPersonAge)]
172. };
173. 
174. IChatClient openaiClient =
175.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
176.     .AsIChatClient();
177. 
178. IChatClient client = new ChatClientBuilder(openaiClient)
179.     .UseDistributedCache(cache)
180.     .UseFunctionInvocation()
181.     .UseOpenTelemetry(sourceName: sourceName, configure: c => c.EnableSensitiveData = true)
182.     .Build();
183. 
184. for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
185. {
186.     Console.WriteLine(await client.GetResponseAsync("How much older is Alice than Bob?", chatOptions));
187. }
188. 
189. [Description("Gets the age of a person specified by name.")]
190. static int GetPersonAge(string personName) =>
191.     personName switch
192.     {
193.         "Alice" => 42,
194.         "Bob" => 35,
195.         _ => 26,
196.     };
197. ```
198. 
199. ### Text embedding generation
200. 
201. ```csharp
202. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
203. 
204. IEmbeddingGenerator<string, Embedding<float>> generator =
205.     new OpenAI.Embeddings.EmbeddingClient("text-embedding-3-small", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
206.     .AsIEmbeddingGenerator();
207. 
208. var embeddings = await generator.GenerateAsync("What is AI?");
209. 
210. Console.WriteLine(string.Join(", ", embeddings[0].Vector.ToArray()));
211. ```
212. 
213. ### Text embedding generation with caching
214. 
215. ```csharp
216. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
217. using Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.Distributed;
218. using Microsoft.Extensions.Caching.Memory;
219. using Microsoft.Extensions.Options;
220. 
221. IDistributedCache cache = new MemoryDistributedCache(Options.Create(new MemoryDistributedCacheOptions()));
222. 
223. IEmbeddingGenerator<string, Embedding<float>> openAIGenerator =
224.     new OpenAI.Embeddings.EmbeddingClient("text-embedding-3-small", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY"))
225.     .AsIEmbeddingGenerator();
226. 
227. IEmbeddingGenerator<string, Embedding<float>> generator = new EmbeddingGeneratorBuilder<string, Embedding<float>>(openAIGenerator)
228.     .UseDistributedCache(cache)
229.     .Build();
230. 
231. foreach (var prompt in new[] { "What is AI?", "What is .NET?", "What is AI?" })
232. {
233.     var embeddings = await generator.GenerateAsync(prompt);
234. 
235.     Console.WriteLine(string.Join(", ", embeddings[0].Vector.ToArray()));
236. }
237. ```
238. 
239. ### Dependency Injection
240. 
241. ```csharp
242. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
243. using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;
244. using Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting;
245. using Microsoft.Extensions.Logging;
246. 
247. // App Setup
248. var builder = Host.CreateApplicationBuilder();
249. builder.Services.AddDistributedMemoryCache();
250. builder.Services.AddLogging(b => b.AddConsole().SetMinimumLevel(LogLevel.Trace));
251. 
252. builder.Services.AddChatClient(services =>
253.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY")).AsIChatClient())
254.     .UseDistributedCache()
255.     .UseLogging();
256. 
257. var app = builder.Build();
258. 
259. // Elsewhere in the app
260. var chatClient = app.Services.GetRequiredService<IChatClient>();
261. Console.WriteLine(await chatClient.GetResponseAsync("What is AI?"));
262. ```
263. 
264. ### Minimal Web API
265. 
266. ```csharp
267. using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
268. 
269. var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
270. 
271. builder.Services.AddChatClient(services =>
272.     new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient("gpt-4o-mini", builder.Configuration["OPENAI_API_KEY"]).AsIChatClient());
273. 
274. builder.Services.AddEmbeddingGenerator(services =>
275.     new OpenAI.Embeddings.EmbeddingClient("text-embedding-3-small", builder.Configuration["OPENAI_API_KEY"]).AsIEmbeddingGenerator());
276. 
277. var app = builder.Build();
278. 
279. app.MapPost("/chat", async (IChatClient client, string message) =>
280. {
281.     var response = await client.GetResponseAsync(message);
282.     return response.Message;
283. });
284. 
285. app.MapPost("/embedding", async (IEmbeddingGenerator<string, Embedding<float>> client, string message) =>
286. {
287.     var response = await client.GenerateAsync(message);
288.     return response[0].Vector;
289. });
290. 
291. app.Run();
292. ```
293. 
294. ## Documentation
295. 
296. Learn how to create a conversational .NET console chat app using an OpenAI or Azure OpenAI model with the [Quickstart - Build an AI chat app with .NET](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/ai/quickstarts/build-chat-app?pivots=openai) documentation.
297. 
298. ## Feedback & Contributing
299. 
300. We welcome feedback and contributions in [our GitHub repo](https://github.com/dotnet/extensions).
